message.body: Yea it's like an in-between. I went out thinking it was going to be soooo cold today from what I heard from the news. It wasn't bad, pretty nice!

I thought it was freezing!! Then again, I was walking a lot. Haha. I went out with my sister. We went from 10th and market to 16th and spruce, then to 20th and spruce, and then to 8th and race. No fun!
Jeez, were you walking for fun?
No. We were meeting Charles and his coworkers for a lunch at monk's cafe. Then we went to yogorino, and then to where Charles parked his car.
Okay makes sense hahah. Monk's Cafe! Is it still as dark inside like the last time we were there?
OMG yes! We walked outside and I was like "wtf! Why is it so bright?!"
Hahahahahah! Good thing we went at night the last time then!
I feel like I'm walking around in the dark right now, I'm walking around looking for bibs right now for my sister and I don't see it!
Haha. Those damned bibs! Just stick a napkin on em. That's what I did if i couldn't find it. Thy always looked so cute...like they were waiting for lobster.
Awwww!
Xuan wants these special ones. She sent me a pic.

I feel horrible because since I worked in a baby room, I feel like I'm just like "ehhh, they'll live!" When I have my baby, I'm going to be like "it's fine!" Whereas everyone will be like "they need this SPECIFIC one!"
Are they eating solids already? That's cray! I feel like they were just born.
I don't blame you! I think napkins are fine too hahah!
I don't think she officially starts them on solids yet. At least I don't think so. I think she's getting these in preparation.

Ohhh. Okay. I don't like those rubber bibs. I prefer the softer plastic ones. The rubber ones are very....not flexible.
But I can't believe they're getting so big. I still can't tell them apart, but they're cute!
Time has flew!!! They're bigger and more alert now. I like babies at these stages. Before they have 8,000 questions to ask every day hahah.
HAHAHA. Their eyes are so big.
They don't have it here!!!!
Boo! Where did you go?
I went to Target.
I don't know how well I'll do with motherhood man.
Haha. You'll have to find a significant other first. That is, if you want. I believe you can do it yourself...I'll help.
Oh I don't know about that. Thanks for the vote of confidence but I don't even have that for myself hahah. I'm with the twins now and they're cute and all, but I'm ready to go
